\b Salon Max Wiring Test Sheet\b0\par
\par
Goal: identify the correct command path and the correct feedback path for a future Raspberry Pi interface.\par
\par
\b Working assumption\b0\par
\tab - Yellow/Blue + Red/Green are the likely command / relay drive wires.\par
\tab - Black + White are the strongest candidate for feedback / status.\par
\tab - Do not use the 230V side for Raspberry Pi feedback.\par
\tab - Do not connect unknown 12V / 18V bed wiring directly to Pi GPIO.\par
\par
\b For each state, record\b0\par
\tab - Y/B to R/G volts\par
\tab - Y/B to R/G continuity\par
\tab - Black to White volts\par
\tab - Black to White continuity\par
\tab - Relay coil side volts\par
\tab - Relay contact side volts\par
\tab - Observed behaviour\par
\par
\b Test states\b0\par
1. Idle / bed not programmed\par
2. Bed started by till\par
3. Emergency stop pressed on bed\par
4. Stopped via till\par
5. Cooldown finished\par
